		<description><![CDATA[If you are asked what the most popular video sharing community is, surely you can only think of Youtube. Who wouldn’t be familiar with its name, especially after several people have already made it big just because the influx of viewable material is endless and widespread? Add to that the reports that daily, 3 billion [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>If you are asked what the most popular video sharing community is, surely you can only think of <a title="Youtube Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/packages/youtube-marketing">Youtube</a>. Who wouldn’t be familiar with its name, especially after several people have already made it big just because the influx of viewable material is endless and widespread? Add to that the reports that daily, 3 billion videos are being viewed. If likened to a disease, the Youtube phenomenon is indeed viral and infectious, affecting millions of lives nonstop.</strong></p>
<p><a href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Youtubelogo.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1164" title="Youtube Marketing" src="http://www.guorillamedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Youtubelogo.png" alt="" width="192" height="192" /></a>In June 2006 alone, which is 5 long years ago, there were already 19.6 unique viewers that were recorded in ratings, how much more now? Social networking has never been active, and businesses have maximized this occurrence as well. Think about it, with so many people going online simultaneously, there is also lots of information that could be handled and shared. As a marketer of products and services, this exposure is beneficial and important in order to breed familiarity among people.</p>
<p>With a market reach that is massive, advertisers need to plot out their schemes so that the necessary angles will be covered. A clear example would be not hurrying things up just for the sake of belonging. Ad placement is very crucial because you need to have those consumers see your ads. Thus, it involves constant research about which site they frequent and the kind of activities they do from time to time in order to match it with your conceptualization and extensive planning. Unpredictability should be conquered because you won’t be able to market your products and services if your audience is not defined down to the specifics.</p>
<p>Another challenge would be the indecisiveness of people. With daily servings of any types of media, a lot of influences would also be going around. People can change preferences so easily that it scares marketers. Thus, the key yet again is research. You can do so by setting up a team that could monitor the doings of those users and possibly pinpoint the reason behind their change of mind.</p>
<p>Marketing moves should be fluid and seamless, complementing each other while at the same time being understandable on its own. Your Youtube account will be your venue for expression, dissemination and collection. You express thoughts and disseminate updates through status posts, and then you collect followers and subscribers. You do all these because you need to, because networking involves having to deal with as many people as you can for the exposure.</p>
<p><a title="Social Media Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com">Social media marketing</a> is becoming known to affect seller and consumer lives alike. Never have communication been this convenient, this fun and this privileged. Take a video for example. Normally, what you can find are postings of song covers that also generate hype. Views may range from a million to the 20’s even, and that’s insane.</p>
<p>What about those who wish to share ‘know-how’ or provide an easier alternative for products being looked for? What about information on the latest? What about them? That’s where you can come in, as a provider of needs for a specific target market.</p>
