			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>An online marketing campaign requires extensive research and rigorous planning. Why? Because you are dealing with a large number of online users and you need to effectively target those who you are aiming for. They are the people who will most likely buy your products and pay for your services, thus a niche should also be established so that your specialization will be highlighted and you will have an identifying factor.</strong></p>
<p>Traditional marketing involves paying for ad placements in televisions, radios and billboards. Although they are still present and are still being used by big corporations and businesses, others are rigorously campaigning online because of the benefits of persistent internet presence. Without it, a good number of customers will be lost, and that is something that businesses do not look forward to experiencing. Who knows, a large percentage of your target audience might be online, ready to receive information that you can offer.</p>
<p>Here, we will shed light to the different online marketing strategies that businesses can use.</p>
<ul>
<li>Search engine optimization is making waves in the online      community nowadays, and more businesses are opening to provide services      like it to businesses. It is considered the most cost effective, ensuring      a concentration of online traffic in your site with the help of search      engines and their results. Algorithms are also important in employing this      kind of strategy, since web contents need to be indexed and then ranked.</li>
<li>Paid advertising meanwhile equates      to paying a service provider for every click garnered by your ad. Since      the number of clicks that can be produced is not fixed, you need to allot      a reasonably priced budget before starting with this technique.</li>
<li><a title="Social Media Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com">Social media marketing</a>, which is      also known as “viral” marketing, is what business use when connected      through <a title="Facebook Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/packages/facebook-marketing">Facebook</a>, <a title="Twitter Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/packages/twitter-marketing">Twitter</a>, <a title="Myspace Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/packages/myspace-marketing">Myspace</a>, <a title="Youtube Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/packages/youtube-marketing">Youtube</a> and the likes. It is reminiscent of a      virus, where its characteristic is spreading like wildfire in a quick span      of time. Thus, this guarantees a quick spread of any information you post      as well, and this is when you are connected with the right people, and at      the right time.</li>
</ul>
<p>Once you go online with your campaigns, you can choose a marketing strategy in which you can concentrate on, with considerations on the timeline, the budget and the immediate effect you can get from it. If you can take it, you can go for everything to ensure a web presence that is scattered and could reach the farthest of places. However, make sure that your campaigns for each are effective so that you won’t sacrifice anything.</p>
<p>With the entire buzz about having the need to establish strong web presence, you can take advantage of the phenomenon by taking into consideration every pointer that you can get to succeed. Do not jump into the bandwagon just because others are doing so. Be a part of it because you want to, and that you can handle it while leveling the business field and competing with other businesses who aim for the same.</p>
