		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.guorillamedia.com/?p=1196</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[A smart Twitter Marketing strategy encompasses different kinds of tactics that businesses can use. Yes, a good number of followers may be crucial to the process, but relevantly so if they are also actively participating in your campaign, and with consistency. Apart from daily postings, Twitter chat proves to be a useful application as well. [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>A smart <a title="Twitter Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/packages/twitter-marketing">Twitter Marketing</a> strategy encompasses different kinds of tactics that businesses can use. Yes, a good number of followers may be crucial to the process, but relevantly so if they are also actively participating in your campaign, and with consistency. Apart from daily postings, Twitter chat proves to be a useful application as well. So if you want any advises and observations about this kind of interaction, read on.</strong></p>
<p><em><strong><a href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/twitter-birds.png"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1136" title="Twitter Marketing" src="http://www.guorillamedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/twitter-birds-300x189.png" alt="" width="300" height="189" /></a></strong></em><em><strong>Hashtags</strong></em> – In sites like <a title="Facebook Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/packages/facebook-marketing">Facebook</a>, tagging involves listing down the name of every person found in a picture. This makes it easier for them to know which photos they belong in. However, in the blogosphere, tags are written as an endnote to categorize an entry and so that whenever a search is made, it can be picked up under that clause. When chatting in Twitter, it still has the same function, reflecting the topic at hand for it to be easily relatable to those involved.</p>
<p><em><strong>Organization</strong></em> &#8211; Whereas there are people who chat randomly, you should hold conferences in consistent days and times. This way, you save yourself the effort of informing people over and over again about what will happen and what’s happening. You can successfully invite more people to participate if they are notified in advance.</p>
<p>Also, there are two formats that are reportedly common and familiar to people. One is the free for all format in which anyone can post a comment or a question, just like in cocktail parties where anyone can just bump into each other and socialize. Meanwhile, another would be involving you as the moderator for having initiated the chat session. You can invite guests to serve as interviewees whereas the attendees observe the conversation. You should brief the speakers of how it will go beforehand so that they won’t get caught off guard or suddenly have a mental block.</p>
<p><em><strong>Available information</strong></em> – Whenever people get curious, they need to know more. Thus, a web page that is dedicated entirely to an information drive would be helpful. In there you can explain the mechanics of the chat sessions, why it is being held and for what purpose, who moderates the chat, etcetera.</p>
<p><em><strong>Recognition</strong></em> &#8211; In all the chat sessions, it is important to note that everything wouldn’t be possible without the participation of the guests and participants. Thus, you can give them due recognition by highlighting parts of conversations that were interesting and listing down active members. Every source of help should be recognized because it allows for a more manageable atmosphere when chats ensue.</p>
<p><em><strong>Archiving </strong></em>– Archiving discussions allows you to look them up again and study your consistency and improvement. Also, any interesting conversation that occurred can be used as a source for your web contents, so never miss a beat.</p>
<p>Reaching out to potential consumers is the key to gaining their trust and approval. Chat sessions in Twitter will strengthen that bond, and sooner pr later you will find yourself full of support from your loyal following. So hop on the discussions and be informed.</p>
