		<description><![CDATA[Over the past few years, there have been numerous reports on the sudden rise to fame of several people, thanks to the online video sharing community known as Youtube. It was in the year 2005 when 3 former employees of Paypal created a free-for-all venue for video uploading and streaming that would soon become a [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Over the past few years, there have been numerous reports on the sudden rise to fame of several people, thanks to the online video sharing community known as <a title="Youtube Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/packages/youtube-marketing">Youtube</a>. It was in the year 2005 when 3 former employees of Paypal created a free-for-all venue for video uploading and streaming that would soon become a phenomenon. It is now evident with how artists and bands are getting their fair share of attention, especially when fans who do not tune in to radios anymore want to listen to their preferred songs, complete with visual effects. Moreover, strangers and nobody’s from all over the world are also getting widespread recognition, thus proving its viral effect.</strong></p>
<p><a href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Youtubelogo.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1164" title="Youtube Marketing" src="http://www.guorillamedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Youtubelogo.png" alt="" width="192" height="192" /></a>It is then safe to assume that apart from the people who simply are in need of a fun viewing experience, people involved with businesses can also take part in this eventful development by doing online marketing through video uploads on Youtube. Why? Because online content is easily disseminated in a matter of seconds from the time it was uploaded. Furthermore, feedbacks are instantaneous and are guaranteed because it is the first site in everyone’s priority when it comes to searching for videos.</p>
<p>Although the quality you get may not exceed standards, it doesn’t really matter since people understand its necessity as a means of sharing, and not of a guaranteed high definition craze. This realization doesn’t downplay its significance for online marketers any less either, so it is still as good as a prospect for brand exposure and awareness.</p>
<p>However, you may say to yourself that if almost every one uses Youtube, then surely there’s a lot of competition to deal with, right? Yes, that’s always part of the scheme. Thus, it is important to realize this well enough to know how to strategize your online campaign despite competing videos that are also hogging some, if not most of the spotlight.</p>
<p>What it takes then is a proper planning of your video sharing immersion. What’s the importance of planning?</p>
<ul>
<li>Organization – Everyone always has to deal with thoughts that      are sometimes full to the brim or sometimes lacking of inspiration.      Filtering out important points is vital to every decision making, thus you      need to plan first what you are going to do and how you will go about it      so you go straight to the point.</li>
<li>Targeting – For every brand’s product line, there is always a      target audience and a target market. Thus, if you plan your strategies by      researching, you will be able to clearly define the purpose of your      campaign and design it accordingly.</li>
<li>Customizing – There are different marketing tools that you can      use at your disposal, and you need to sort out through the list so that      you can identify which will work best in terms of the timeline and the      financial backing you have.</li>
<li>Saving – If you know what you are doing all along, chances are,      you would be able to detect the slightest twists that are pulling you away      from the objective. Also, once guided, you not only save time and effort,      you also spare yourself from wasting your hard earned money.</li>
</ul>
