			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Since its launch way back in 2004, Facebook has now grown tremendously and presently caters to over half a billion users. From its exclusivity to Harvard students, it successfully invaded different universities and now is open for everybody regardless of gender, race, country and beliefs. In fact, those differences are what make it interesting especially with the persisting availability of communication between any two persons or more in a convenient manner.</strong></p>
<p>Who benefits from Facebook? First, the people in general who want to make profiles and use it as a venue for identity and for self expression. Also, there are the advertisers and businesses that enjoy the privilege of their ads being broadcasted to a large number of masses simultaneously. This is the main reason why it is beneficial to set up a <a title="Facebook Marketing" href="http://www.guorillamedia.com/packages/facebook-marketing">Facebook marketing</a> campaign, add to that its affordability and the low cost maintenance it requires.</p>
<p>So how will you start your campaign in the internet’s most used social networking site?</p>
<ol>
<li>The first step would be to set up an account. Remember that      your brand may be associated to you, but you do not need to use your      personal account for your venture. Separate your private life and dedicate      one that is entirely for business. Meanwhile, your e-mail contacts can      easily be imported and they will be notified through ‘friend suggestion’      about your newly made account.</li>
<li>Aside from your profile, which accepts friend requests, a      corresponding page would also prove useful. People only need to “Like”      your page to subscribe to your posts and updates, thus it is more      convenient for them.</li>
<li>Every account requires a profile picture of the owner. If you      already have an existing logo of your business, use it for easy recall in      future online encounters. It is advantageous to have a logo that is      professional looking but still has a creative and classy appeal to it.      Like they always say, first impressions last.</li>
<li>Online users usually look at info tabs first to get to know the      owner of the account. Thus, you can then edit your page and write a      description of what your business does. Better make it brief and concise      while being engaging than lengthy so that people. Also, cut it down to the      essentials and do not forget to use important and relevant keywords      because the tabs are still detectable for search engine indexing.</li>
<li>There are also different Page applications at your disposal.      For example, if you do not want the users to be greeted with simply a text      page, the Static Facebook Markup Language (FBML) feature will allow you to      add more tabs and use codes/html for the posting of flash or images. You      can then edit the settings as to which tab you want to be seen when users      view your Page for the first time, while being unsubscribed still.</li>
<li>URL’s are very important because it will be the key to finding      your site when just being typed in internet browsers. People surely can’t      memorize the default url of your Facebook profile (which may have an      extension like this: 326727833086?ref=sgm&amp;ajaxpipe=1&amp;__a=7), so immediately change it to your own business name. Thus, you      will then be known as <a href="http://www.facebook.com/username">www.facebook.com/username</a> in the network. Easy recall, easy viewing.</li>
</ol>
